data.title: Fundación Camilo José Cela
data.text:
Awards

Medals, street and commemorative plaques, diplomas (among them 25 honoris causa doctorates), sculptures, trophies, symbolic keys to cities, insignias and a small textile collection of uniforms and robes that make up a set of original value and significance. It was assembled by possibly one of the most awarded authors in Spanish literature ever, recognized as such by the Guinness Book of World Records in 1994, having at the time 182 certified recognitions.
